5 But among the Romans, there was not so much allowed to the soldiers under the old republi03 as' sufficiently appears from what we have said above. In the civil wars, they began to be more indulged. Thus we read that Equulanum was plundered by the soldiers of Sulla. And Caesar, in Lucan, gives up the camp of Pompey after the battle of Pharsalia to be plundered. The soldiers of Octavius and Antony plundered the camp of Brutus and Cassius.
